				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Modifier Stacking<a name="19594"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 6 04 1:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The instrument augments from LDoN count as a &quot;regular instrument&quot;.  That is, if you have the 1.6 modifier Wind Aug on your BP, you get 1.6.  If you equip a 2.2 mod Bloodstained Flute, you get 2.2.... NOT 3.8.  They do NOT add, the highest wins.
<br />

<br />
Now, there ARE some items that ADD to modifiers.  The Voice of the Serpent, for example, ADDS to your singing modifier, as does the song: Amplification.  So, your Epic would be Singing 1.8, Amp (varies by level) would ADD like .8 or something, VotS adds another point-something...  giving you a very nice Singing modifier indeed.
<br />

<br />
If you look at the linkie that say &quot;Instruments&quot; here, you will see the complete lists.  Generally speaking, if the item says Zero-Point-Something... it is an ADDATIVE modifier.  If it is 1.8, 2.2, 2.6.... it is almost certainly what I described above as a &quot;regular instrument modifer&quot;, with the highest one winning, and NOT stacking.
<br />

<br />
I hope this help a bit.
<br />

<br />
Klapton / Scherzo <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-17.gif" border="0" alt="" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
