				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Modifier Stacking<a name="19605"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 6 04 2:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hehe....lets keep this simple and non-confusing.
<br />

<br />
Instrument modifiers do not stack.  Only the highest one will take effect.  (The same as having multiple haste items).
<br />

<br />
Singing is the only skill we have that has the ability to get increased from a spell/song effect.  Bards have a discipline, Puretone, to boost all instrument skills.
<br />

<br />
1.) Our lv30 Amplification song.
<br />
2.) A spell effect from certain items (Like Voice of the Serpent)
<br />

<br />
Voice of the Serpent is a right-click item that cast &quot;Resonance&quot; on you.  This spell boosts your singing skill.  And since any stat from songs stacks with stats from a spell, with the exception of haste, Amplification will boost your singing skill even further.
<br />

<br />
Sooo...those items are not instrument modifier items, they just have an effect that boosts the skill.
<br />

<br />
This clears any confusion from statements like &quot;sometimes they do, sometime they don't.&quot;
<br />

<br />
Unless I'm unaware of something else, there are only 2 items in the game that provide a &quot;Spell Effect&quot; to boost our singing skill:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=8215">Voice of the Serpent</a>
<br />
<a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/item.html?id=26574">Shadowsong Cloak</a></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
